textJson.text:
Ibaraki-Douji has a large amount of Total HP, but it will not regenerate between battles.

Damage will be inflicted to Ibaraki-Douji by all Masters participating in the event.

Battles with Ibaraki-Douji have a turn limit. 
When the turn limit is reached, the battle will end automatically. Deal as much damage as you can before you run out of turns.

Furthermore, it will not be possible to continue lost battles against Ibaraki-Douji.

Magical Girls have a large HP pool called an Episode Countdown. Decrease the Episode Countdown by dealing damage to a Magical Girl. The decreased Episode Countdown will be carried over to the next battle.
Magical Girls are weak to either Arts or Buster attacks. Choose Command Cards that exploit these weak points to deal massive damage to them.

Battles with Magical Girls have turn limits.
The battle will end automatically when the turn limit is reached.

If your party is incapacitated, you will not be able to Continue, but the Episode Countdown decreased in battle will be reflected and the following rewards will be issued:
Bond Points, Master EXP, Mystic Code EXP, Friend Points, Battle Drops

If you choose Withdraw from the Battle Menu, the Episode Countdown you reduced in battle will not be reflected and no rewards will be issued.

In World End Match, damage dealt will be reflected on the Episode Countdown gauge even if you lose the battle, and the following rewards will be issued:
Bond Points, Master EXP, Mystic Code EXP, Friend Points, Battle Drops

The amount of rewards obtained will vary with the amount of damage dealt.

Even if you defeat the Demon Gods, as long as the gauge remains, they will continue to resurrect.

The top screen shows a gauge and how many times they have been defeated. The gauge will decrease each time they are defeated. 
The number of times other Masters have defeated them will also be displayed continuously.  

Let's all work together to defeat the Demon Gods until the gauge goes completely down!

In addition to the HP gauge that regenerates at the start of every battle, Ibaraki-Douji has a gauge called Total HP.

Damage inflicted to Ibaraki-Douji by all Masters participating in the event will be applied to the Total HP gauge and carried over between battles.

Battles against Ibaraki-Douji have a turn limit.

When the turn limit is reached, the battle will end automatically. Damage dealt up to that point will be awarded as Damage Points.

Continue will not be available if your entire party is wiped out.
If you choose Withdraw from the Battle Menu, Damage Points will not be awarded.

Within Raid Battles, the following rewards will be issued even if you lose the battle:
Damage Points, Bond Points, Master EXP, Mystic Code EXP, Friend Points, Battle Drops

The amount of rewards obtained will vary with the amount of damage dealt.

- About Exhibition Quests -

Exhibition Quests are [FF0000]Ultra High Difficulty Quests[-] for advanced players.

To clear them, you will have to carefully analyze the enemy and consider Party Formation, Mystic Code, Skills, Noble Phantasms, and all other factors.

[FF9800]Try not to be discouraged, and keep trying until you can defeat the enemy![-]

Since you have no active Doujin Production Quests, the [Loop] The Melancholy of a Dramatic Demon has been unlocked at the ServantFes Site. Please proceed by completing this quest.

*As this is a Loop, no Quest completion rewards will be granted.

Enemies that show up in Sacrilege Tetrahedron have a large HP pool called a Total HP. Dealing damage to an enemy will deplete its HP as well as the the Total HP. The decreased Total HP will be carried over to the next battle.

Battles against enemies in "Sacrilege Tetrahedron" have turn limits. The battle will end automatically when the turn count reaches 0.

If your party is incapacitated, you will not be able to Continue, but the Total HP depleted in battle will be reflected and the following rewards will be issued:
Master EXP, Mystic Code EXP, and Friend Points.

If you choose Withdraw from the Battle Menu, the Total HP you reduced in battle will not be reflected and no rewards will be issued.

In battles against enemies in Sacrilege Tetrahedron, the following rewards will be issued even if you lose the battle:
Master EXP, Mystic Code EXP, Friend Points

- About Exhibition Quests -

Exhibition Quests are [FF0000]Ultra High Difficulty Quests[-] for advanced players.

To clear them, you will have to carefully analyze the enemy and consider Party Formation, Mystic Code, Skills, Noble Phantasms, and all other factors.

[FF9800]Try not to be discouraged, and keep trying until you can defeat the enemy![-]

Even if you defeat the Great Oni Vermilion Dragon, they will resurrect as long as the gauge remains.

The gauge at the top of the screen shows how many times they have been defeated. The gauge will decrease each time they are defeated.
The number of times other Masters have defeated them will also be reflected in real time.

Let's all work together to defeat the Great Oni Vermilion Dragon until the gauge reaches zero!
